      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Scholar" href="/users/neorei">neorei</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Scholar">Scholar</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">122 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Good  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">First of all, I’m doing this because I’m bored, and I can’t sleep. Stupid game.  I know there is better guides out there about crafting but I will (or at least try) to show you how to craft several crafts without spending too much money. Well at least up to level 10, after that you are on your own. <br /> <br />Here is a link to my amory: <br /><a href="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1652854" title="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1652854" rel="external nofollow">http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1652854</a> <br /> <br />my main craft is Amory which is level 17 but I managed to get goldsmithing, Blacksmith, leatherworking all up to 10 and the others to 5-8 (with the help of leves) <br /> <br />Anyways here is my guide. Please don’t be too mean or critical on me, I’m doing this just to help the community.   Constructive criticism is much appreciative. <br /> <br />Thing I’ve notice that there is certain tiers or pattern to the crafting, I notice that some crafts support other crafts from level 1-10.  First you have to start off by mining which can be tedious at first but will help you out in the long run. <br /> <br />Since I’m from the most gangster place called Limsa Lominsa or what we gangsters and thugs call LL, I’ll be using that as my area to mine and craft.  You can apply this to any other 1-10 areas in FFXIV! <br /> <br />First of all mine, this will help your crafting (at least the armor/black/goldsmithing) out very much because the ores you will be getting will help you craft.  Keep mining around the 1-10 area, while you are doing that you can switch around and kill cobblers for ores (in the uldah area) or sheep/dodos for skins to later use for leatherworking.  I average about 5-10 ores of copper and a few tin while mining.  Keep stacking that various copper ore and tin ores!  Also another thing is you’ll need shards and mining is a great way to gather up shards.  Fire, Wind, earth shards are the shards you’ll be looking for. <br /> <br />Anyways before you do anything! Stop and look at yourself in the mirror and say these words <br /> <br />“I’m good enough, I’m smart enough, and god darnit, people like me” <br /> <br />Out of the way? Good. <br /> <br />During this I’ve added crafting leves,  @ start you will get 1-3 leves of each craft, raising the difficulty every 5 levels you are in that craft.   By this time you should be level 5 mining and be able to mine yellow copper/copper ores/tin ores without any trouble. <br /> <br />Okay I’m sleepy, incoming horribad grammar.  <br /> <br />Each being leve should take you to level 4-5 which is a big help so if your level 1.  you should accept the following leves.  <br /> <br />Blacksmithing <br /> <br />Goldsmithing <br /> <br />Armorer <br /> <br />FILL THIS UP!!! DON’T HATE GO 8/8. YEAH! After you’re finished with all of that, now heres the part you start wasting away all that hard work. <br /> <br />NOW BRING OUT THE GOLDSMITH WEATHERED HAMMER OF MIGHT!!!! <br /> <br />Anywho.  Now by this time, you should be able to craft copper nuggets!! (this is the kinda expensive part because it does involve a fire crystal, unless you farm them!) <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-nugget?id=147" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-nugget?id=147" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-nugget?id=147</a> <br /> <br />Using 4 yellow ores and a fire crystal you will be able to make 12 copper nuggets!  Try to save your fire crystals because it’ll help you out later. While doing this you should be gaining about 200-400 skillpoints and 1000-1600 EXP! YUMMY!!!! <br /> <br />You should be about level 7-8 in goldsmithing, STOP RIGHT THERE BUDDY. <br /> <br />Okay I maybe wrong, because honestly, I can’t remember which way I took here.  You can either level up making copper ingots as a Goldsmither , Blacksmith, Armor. <br /> <br />Let’s go blacksmith. <br /> <br />Copper ingots <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-ingot?id=120" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-ingot?id=120" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-ingot?id=120</a> <br /> <br />Keep using that recipe till level 8. Also another thing don’t kill all the nuggets, you need some for later. <br /> <br />NOW BRING OUT THE MIGHT WEATHERED ARMORER HAMMER OF PROTECTION. <br /> <br />Okay got copper ingots? Good. <br /> <br />Now do these 2 crafts <br /> <br />Copper wire. Using the ingots. <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-wire?id=51" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-wire?id=51" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-wire?id=51</a> <br /> <br />after you are done with that, you can go ahead and make these <br /> <br />Copper rings: Using the Wire. <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-rings?id=58" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-rings?id=58" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-rings?id=58</a> <br /> <br />Copper ringz G!!!!! <br /> <br />Oh yeah you do need guild support for this (both wires and rings), since I said we’re doing this in LL, guess where the armorer guild is at, yup you got it. It’s in LL. <br /> <br />This should take you level 8-10 armorer depending how good you are (this was during the whole rapid spamming pre nerf) <br /> <br />Now with using those copper rings you go back to gold smithing and BAM <br />Copper wristlets <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-wristlet?id=246" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-wristlet?id=246" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/copper-wristlet?id=246</a> <br /> <br />hopefully you save some nuggets from when you were making the ingots.  You can either sell them or vendor them, up to you really but this should take your goldsmithing up to 10. <br /> <br />NOW NEOREI WE STILL HAVE 2-3 LEVELS IN BLACKSMITHING TO GO. <br /> <br />Oh yeah by this time armorer and goldsmithing should be about level 10.  This the part where you use all that copper and tin ore you have been saving up. <br /> <br />Smash them to bronze nuggets, by using 3 copper ores and 1 tin nugget. <br /> <br />Rule of thumb, have 4 tin ores for every stack of copper or you have. <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-nugget?id=122" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-nugget?id=122" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-nugget?id=122</a> <br /> <br />again, this does consist of using fire crystals, which are expensive. Unless you farm them woot woot. <br /> <br />Since you’ve made a lot of nuggets, it’s time to ingot them  <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-ingot?id=101" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-ingot?id=101" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-ingot?id=101</a> <br /> <br />this should take you to level 10, at least.  If you have a few nuggets laying around, I suggest making these <br /> <br /><a href="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-needle?id=105" title="http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-needle?id=105" rel="external nofollow">http://ffxiv.yg.com/recipe/bronze-needle?id=105</a> <br /> <br />cheap as ****! <br /> <br />Now you should have level 10 in 3 crafts and a ton of bronze ingots to level your armorer to 20!!! My suggestions to repeat this until you get to 14 armorer because you may break a lot of thoese ingots you have been working hard on.  #1 thing is that you got to mine,  buying from vendor sucks and it’s expensive, even with this guide it should help a lot. And hopefully it helps a lot. <br /> <br />Anyways I’m sleepy, I’ll check the comments and bitching out tomorrow morning, if you have suggestions or even want to add something, post. <br /> <br />tl;dr<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Neorei  <br />shiva server <br />75PLD/61DRK/37WAR <br />Neorei Dawnbreaker <br />Cornelia Sever <br /><a href="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1652854" title="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1652854" rel="external nofollow">http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1652854</a> <br />Neorei <br />Skywall server <br /><a href="http://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Skywall&amp;cn=Neorei" title="http://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Skywall&amp;cn=Neorei" rel="external nofollow">http://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Skywall&amp;cn=Neorei</a></div></div>
